Amazon Customer
5.0 out of 5 stars Powerful and effective
Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2023
Verified Purchase
Bought to replace a very similar version from another Amazon vendor. This new one is way better!

Stronger, smoother.

Old one lasted several years of daily use. I think what killed old one was pulsing the button to regulate speed. I disassembled motor, and found the thin wire used as a motor brush had melted.

Electric motors use way more to spin up than they use to keep spinning. So pulsing the button is like making it start up over and over. Lots of heat. So this new one I'm going to be more careful not to do that.

Old one would sometimes be more powerful than I wanted. So I'd use the button to regulate speed. New one is even more powerful, but also smoother.

Old one oscillated more. Basically it wobbled. In retrospect, it probably had a bent or out of balance impeller. I thought it was meant to be that way. New one just spins, no wobble.

So new one being more powerful isn't as much of an issue. Still, it'll try to overflow the cup I'm using to froth if its smaller cup.

My method: pour product into cup. Microwave about 25-30 sec. Froth until full foam (30-45 sec).

I use plant based creamer. Certain brands seem to foam better than others, some not at all, despite all being almond milk based. So experiment with different brands. I seem to have good success with Silk brand.

The frothing process, at first it seems like nothing is happening. Its spinning at high rate, flung up sides of cup threatening to overspill, and it just keeps doing that like its not working. Then eventually it changes and starts to foam. Soon after its as foamed as it'll get.

There does seem to be a minimum amount of creamer that will actually foam up. Below that amount, its not going to foam. Ever. That minimum amount is probably a bit more than you'd want to use for a single cup.

So either make two cups at a time, leave the extra for your next cup (by then it'll lose its foam, and likely won't foam as well a second time), or just enjoy more foam per cup than is really needed.
